any better, am I?

16:51.730 --> 16:53.999
It's okay.
I don't mind.

16:55.332 --> 16:57.569
What's your favorite part
about Christmas?

17:00.372 --> 17:03.406
I love decorating.

17:03.408 --> 17:06.208
Stringing up the lights,
hanging the wreaths

17:06.210 --> 17:08.877
and, oh, putting the ornaments
on the tree.

17:08.880 --> 17:12.515
And I love the music.

17:12.517 --> 17:17.753
I love dancing and singing
and making cookies.

17:17.756 --> 17:18.855
Every year,

17:18.857 --> 17:20.390
my brother takes me out

17:20.392 --> 17:22.191
and I pick out my present

17:22.193 --> 17:25.294
and then he always
gets it for me.

17:25.296 --> 17:27.296
He seems like
a really good brother.

17:27.298 --> 17:28.698
The best.

17:28.700 --> 17:31.367
And it's just been the two of you
since you were six years old?

17:31.369 --> 17:35.738
Oh, we had an uncle...
watch us for a while.

17:35.740 --> 17:37.306
I didn't like him.

17:37.308 --> 17:38.408
But, it's...

17:38.410 --> 17:43.880
He's gone now,
so it's just me and Edward.

17:43.882 --> 17:47.151
I don't know if I could have gone
through something like that.

17:47.153 --> 17:48.887
You must be really strong.

17:50.722 --> 17:51.991
I like you.

17:54.693 --> 17:56.128
I like you, too.

17:56.896 --> 18:00.097
I actually have to go.

18:00.099 --> 18:02.398
