18:51.383 --> 18:52.818
Yeah...

18:57.456 --> 18:58.756
How long?

18:58.758 --> 19:01.759
I just have to pick up a couple samples.
10 minutes, tops.

19:01.761 --> 19:03.494
Or less.
I don't know.

19:03.496 --> 19:05.195
I want to go home
and play with my toy.

19:05.197 --> 19:06.632
I know you do.

19:10.903 --> 19:12.302
Stay in the car.

19:24.184 --> 19:25.351
Yay!

19:58.018 --> 19:59.349
Hi.

19:59.351 --> 20:00.352
Hi!

20:01.888 --> 20:03.453
Are you all alone?

20:03.455 --> 20:04.590
No.

20:07.060 --> 20:08.525
Good morning.

20:08.527 --> 20:10.230
What can we get filled
for you today?

20:37.057 --> 20:38.389
Are you okay?

20:38.391 --> 20:41.292
Pew, pew, pew, pew, pew.

20:41.294 --> 20:43.061
Choo, choo, choo, choo.

20:43.063 --> 20:44.729
Whoosh!

20:44.731 --> 20:47.165
Shh...

20:47.167 --> 20:48.466
See?

20:48.468 --> 20:49.968
That didn't take so long.

20:49.970 --> 20:52.804
Good. Can we go home
and play now?

20:52.806 --> 20:54.306
What is with you today?

21:16.897 --> 21:18.765
Are you gonna help me
with any of this?!

21:21.369 --> 21:22.533
No.

21:58.673 --> 22:01.842
I have a surprise for you!

22:03.644 --> 22:04.712
I don't want it.

22:05.980 --> 22:09.083
Fine.
I won't spoil it, then.

22:10.318 --> 22:13.285
How about we
play a game instead?

22:13.287 --> 22:15.854
Don't you like it
when we play games?

22:15.856 --> 22:18.726
Go... fuck yourself.

22:20.061 --> 22:22.194
That's not a very nice
thing to say.

22:39.580 --> 22:41.316
Now you play.

22:42.384 --> 22:47.119
I can't even...
I can't even move.

22:47.121 --> 22:48.789
I'll help you.

23:00.801 --> 23:02.770
You can't do this forever.

23:04.373 --> 23:06.375
Who said anything about forever?

23:08.076 --> 23:10.245
You're my Christmas toy.

23:18.519 --> 23:20.588
That hat looks so good on you!

23:22.391 --> 23:24.059
What do you wanna play?!

23:26.294 --> 23:28.962
Are you ticklish?!

23:32.167 --> 23:33.900
I know you like it,

23:33.902 --> 23:35.768
- or why would you be laughing?!
- Stop it!

23:35.770 --> 23:38.306
What do you want to do, then?!

23:40.842 --> 23:43.512
I just wanna go home.

23:45.280 --> 23:47.613
I don't think
you'll feel that way...

23:47.615 --> 23:49.449
...after you see
what I got for you.

24:31.327 --> 24:32.727
What are you looking at?

24:35.664 --> 24:36.865
I'm waiting.

24:37.666 --> 24:38.733
For what?

24:39.535 --> 24:41.002
It's a surprise.

24:41.937 --> 24:44.005
You know I don't like surprises.

24:53.014 --> 24:54.783
You have to...

24:56.486 --> 24:59.388
...set a third place at dinner.

25:00.922 --> 25:02.191
What are you talking about?

25:03.359 --> 25:05.593
I invited a guest.

25:05.595 --> 25:07.330
You invited a guest?

25:08.164 --> 25:09.096
What the fuck
were you thinking?

25:09.098 --> 25:11.731
- I just wanted to have...
- No!

25:11.733 --> 25:13.766
Who did you even invite?!

25:13.768 --> 25:15.436
- Roy.
- Roy?

25:15.438 --> 25:17.071
From coffee, Roy?

25:17.073 --> 25:19.874
I told you next year!

25:19.876 --> 25:23.210
But he's friends with Jason.

25:23.212 --> 25:25.712
I thought
they could play together.

25:25.714 --> 25:27.882
You have no idea
how bad this is.

25:27.884 --> 25:31.285
If Roy finds out
Jason is here...

25:31.287 --> 25:33.154
Call him and tell him
not to come.

25:33.156 --> 25:34.824
Do it now!

25:36.259 --> 25:40.396
- But he-he's 10 minutes away.
- Fuck!

25:41.731 --> 25:44.198
I-I'm sorry.

25:44.200 --> 25:47.234
I don't want us
to get in trouble.

25:55.378 --> 25:57.146
We're not gonna
get into trouble.

25:59.482 --> 26:00.883
I'll take care of it.

26:38.455 --> 26:40.457
I'm really sorry
about all of this.

26:41.625 --> 26:43.627
It's just
for a little while longer.

26:46.129 --> 26:47.429
How are you feeling?

26:50.267 --> 26:53.970
How the fuck...
do you think I'm feeling?

26:55.771 --> 26:59.641
You're right, you're right.

27:24.301 --> 27:27.037
Again? Do you really want
to die or starvation?

27:28.772 --> 27:30.305
Well, you're never gonna
get out of here

27:30.307 --> 27:33.477
if you die of hunger.

27:34.978 --> 27:37.545
There you go.

27:37.547 --> 27:39.583
That's a good boy.

27:43.053 --> 27:44.953
If you let me go,

27:44.955 --> 27:47.188
I won't tell anyone
what happened.

27:47.190 --> 27:50.493
I won't tell.
I'll just live my life.

27:50.495 --> 27:53.328
Emilia would kill me
if I let you go.

27:53.330 --> 27:55.500
You're her favorite toy.

27:56.800 --> 28:00.235
How the fuck can you let her
get away with this shit?

28:00.237 --> 28:04.839
Whoa, whoa, hey. Be careful!

28:04.841 --> 28:06.843
Careful.

28:10.847 --> 28:13.048
Do you have a fever?

28:13.050 --> 28:14.215
Hmm.

28:14.217 --> 28:16.285
We're gonna have
to take care of that.

28:25.263 --> 28:27.231
I have a favor to ask.

28:28.865 --> 28:31.434
We have a guest
coming tonight...

28:31.436 --> 28:32.934
...and I don't want to
have to gag you.

28:32.936 --> 28:34.370
You need me to be quiet.

28:34.372 --> 28:37.906
Yeah. I'll do it for you.

28:37.908 --> 28:40.044
If you help me get out of here.

28:40.877 --> 28:43.081
I can't promise you that.

28:44.782 --> 28:46.415
There you go.

28:46.417 --> 28:47.951
Yeah.

28:52.123 --> 28:53.825
Are you going to be quiet?

28:55.560 --> 28:57.495
I can't promise you that.

29:01.132 --> 29:03.599
Why do you-
why do you do this for her?

29:03.601 --> 29:06.137
She's my sister.

29:07.305 --> 29:10.573
Your sister is insane.

29:17.582 --> 29:20.485
Don't talk about her
like that.

29:51.750 --> 29:54.016
You literally live
off the map.

30:25.150 --> 30:26.151
Hello?

30:27.753 --> 30:29.555
- Emilia?
- Hey!

30:30.222 --> 30:31.688
Hi!

30:31.690 --> 30:33.223
You must be Emilia's brother.

30:33.225 --> 30:34.758
Edward, yeah.

30:34.760 --> 30:35.725
And you're Roy.

30:35.727 --> 30:37.227
That's me.

30:37.229 --> 30:38.395
It's great to meet you.

30:38.397 --> 30:39.930
The house is over here.

30:39.932 --> 30:41.064
I thought I heard something.

30:41.066 --> 30:43.333
Thought maybe Emilia
was in there.

30:43.335 --> 30:44.734
She's inside.

30:44.736 --> 30:45.939
Oh.

30:46.738 --> 30:48.338
You look familiar.
Have we met?

30:48.340 --> 30:49.606
I doubt it.

30:49.608 --> 30:52.342
I could swear I've
seen you somewhere.

30:52.344 --> 30:54.544
Were you in the pharmacy
this morning?

30:54.546 --> 30:55.479
No.

30:55.481 --> 30:57.447
I guess I just have
one of those faces.

30:57.449 --> 30:59.751
I guess so.

31:02.554 --> 31:04.621
You wanna come inside
and see Emilia?

31:04.623 --> 31:06.826
Yes, that would be perfect.

31:08.093 --> 31:11.363
Oh, Emilia!
Your little friend is here.

31:16.435 --> 31:17.467
Hi.

31:17.469 --> 31:19.069
Hi.

31:19.071 --> 31:21.404
It's good to see you again.
You look beautiful.

31:21.406 --> 31:22.876
Thanks.

31:30.249 --> 31:31.214
Follow me.

31:31.216 --> 31:32.249
Where are we going?

31:32.251 --> 31:33.620
You'll see.

31:39.959 --> 31:43.128
I love Christmas more than
anything in the world.

31:50.570 --> 31:52.204
Sit down.

31:53.105 --> 31:55.408
I wanna
show you something special.

33:43.984 --> 33:46.451
Is everything okay
with your brother?

33:46.453 --> 33:47.488
What do you mean?

33:48.389 --> 33:51.222
I don't know,
he just seems... off.

33:51.224 --> 33:54.226
He's got a lot on his mind.

33:54.228 --> 33:57.031
And he worries about me.

33:58.132 --> 33:59.464
Hmm.

34:08.143 --> 34:11.311
Actually, could you point me
to the bathroom?

34:54.521 --> 34:55.790
What the...

34:56.824 --> 34:58.658
What are you doing in here?

34:58.660 --> 35:00.394
Uh...

35:01.428 --> 35:03.096
I was just looking
for the bathroom.

35:03.098 --> 35:06.498
This clearly isn't the bathroom.
This is my workspace.

35:06.500 --> 35:07.934
I know.
I was curious.

35:07.936 --> 35:10.203
Well, you shouldn't be in here
without a mask.

35:10.205 --> 35:11.740
Oh.
Should I be taking something?

35:12.941 --> 35:15.007
You didn't eat anything
while you were in here, did you?

35:15.009 --> 35:16.809
No, of course not.

35:16.811 --> 35:18.378
Well then, you should be fine.

35:20.582 --> 35:22.380
The bathroom's this way.

35:35.096 --> 35:36.798
Just stay for dinner.

35:47.475 --> 35:49.408
What do you think?

35:49.410 --> 35:51.344
About what?

35:51.346 --> 35:52.514
Roy.

35:55.917 --> 35:57.385
I want him.

35:58.853 --> 36:00.655
I thought so.

36:01.890 --> 36:04.390
Is that okay?

36:12.767 --> 36:14.203
Do you mean it?

36:17.505 --> 36:19.273
Merry Christmas.

36:25.981 --> 36:29.382
Roy, I want to show you
something outside.

36:29.384 --> 36:31.018
Okay. Cool.

36:31.020 --> 36:32.654
Dinner in 15.

36:33.255 --> 36:34.687
Looking forward to it.

36:40.129 --> 36:42.164
Hmm.

36:49.972 --> 36:52.773
Those don't even look safe.
Do you swing on those?

36:52.775 --> 36:54.610
Obviously.

37:05.254 --> 37:07.420
Do you get a lot
of visitors out here?

37:07.422 --> 37:10.826
No, not many.

37:11.460 --> 37:14.127
I have to invite them

37:14.129 --> 37:17.130
and I'm not allowed to have
too many people come over.

37:17.132 --> 37:18.334
Aren't allowed?

37:19.535 --> 37:23.904
Edward says you never know
what people are capable of.

37:23.906 --> 37:25.606
He's right about that.

37:27.710 --> 37:29.576
You've lived here
your entire life?

37:29.578 --> 37:30.978
Yup.

37:30.980 --> 37:33.916
At least as long
as I can remember.

37:35.017 --> 37:37.584
Do you work?
Do you have a job?

37:37.586 --> 37:38.721
No.

37:39.622 --> 37:41.989
It would be too hard
for me and Edward

37:41.991 --> 37:44.091
to both have jobs,

37:44.093 --> 37:46.462
since we only have
the one car.

37:47.563 --> 37:49.997
So when he goes to work
you go with him?

37:49.999 --> 37:51.165
Well...

37:51.167 --> 37:53.303
He usually just works from home.

37:54.337 --> 37:57.673
He does some kind of research
with medicine.

37:58.807 --> 38:01.144
I don't really understand it.

38:03.445 --> 38:06.513
So when we met
for coffee this morning...

38:06.515 --> 38:07.951
...was he with you?

38:09.852 --> 38:11.121
Yeah.

38:12.588 --> 38:16.057
He was there the whole time.

38:16.059 --> 38:18.627
Shh.

38:19.695 --> 38:21.896
I knew I knew him
from somewhere.

38:21.898 --> 38:23.730
Why did he lie about that?

38:23.732 --> 38:25.465
Well...

38:25.467 --> 38:27.467
People think it's weird,

38:27.469 --> 38:29.837
me living with him,
so...

38:29.839 --> 38:33.376
...he pretends he isn't there
when I meet people.

38:36.112 --> 38:37.814
So... where did you meet Jason?

38:38.647 --> 38:40.715
You ask so many questions!

38:40.717 --> 38:42.884
I'm serious!

38:42.886 --> 38:46.254
If you want the answer,
you have to catch me.

38:46.256 --> 38:49.123
Okay. If that's how
you're gonna play it.

38:55.432 --> 38:58.333
Got you! Now you have to
answer my question.

38:58.335 --> 39:00.702
No! Let me go!

39:00.704 --> 39:01.869
You giving up already?

39:11.715 --> 39:14.615
- I'm sorry. I thought we were...
- It's fine.

39:19.756 --> 39:25.560
I met Jason... in the
parking lot at the pharmacy.

39:25.562 --> 39:27.562
Edward was inside

39:27.564 --> 39:30.031
picking up some medicine
for work

39:30.033 --> 39:31.433
and I was waiting.

39:31.435 --> 39:34.771
Jason was walking past and....

39:35.839 --> 39:37.475
...he said I looked beautiful...

39:38.575 --> 39:40.643
...and that he'd like
to take me out.

39:41.878 --> 39:46.415
I got a napkin out of the car
and wrote my number on it.

39:46.417 --> 39:47.650
That was it.

39:48.551 --> 39:49.652
Okay.

39:50.687 --> 39:52.388
I didn't mean to scare you.

39:56.327 --> 39:58.329
Dinner's probably ready.

40:02.299 --> 40:04.266
We'll start with this.

40:04.268 --> 40:06.601
The ham will be ready
any minute.

40:06.603 --> 40:08.937
I was just telling Emilia
how amazing everything looks.

40:08.939 --> 40:11.040
Well, it tastes even better.

40:11.042 --> 40:12.276
Can't wait.

40:15.413 --> 40:16.679
Wait!

40:17.314 --> 40:18.981
It's almost Christmas.

40:18.983 --> 40:21.116
We have to say
what we're thankful for.

40:21.118 --> 40:22.386
I'll start.

40:23.854 --> 40:25.754
I'm thankful for

40:25.756 --> 40:27.322
this delicious food

40:27.324 --> 40:29.058
that's on the table
in front of us.

40:29.060 --> 40:30.526
And...

40:30.528 --> 40:35.197
...also I'm thankful that Roy could
join us and make it for dinner.

40:35.199 --> 40:38.434
We're both really glad
to have you here.

40:38.436 --> 40:41.703
And I'm thankful that it's my
favorite time of the year!

40:41.705 --> 40:44.807
Everything is good
at Christmas time.

40:44.809 --> 40:47.812
Okay!
Edward, you're next.

40:49.647 --> 40:51.182
I...

40:54.618 --> 40:57.321
...am thankful
for my sister, Emilia.

40:58.756 --> 41:01.790
You've been the brightest part of
my life for a long, long time.

41:03.127 --> 41:05.994
Seeing you happy
is what I live for.

41:05.996 --> 41:07.832
I would do anything for you.

41:10.368 --> 41:11.834
So I'm thankful
that you're in my life,

41:11.836 --> 41:13.838
and that you keep me focused
on the good things.

41:15.106 --> 41:17.039
I'm also thankful that the
horrible, negative people

41:17.041 --> 41:20.310
who used to be in our lives are
no longer a part of this family.

41:20.312 --> 41:21.979
Oh, me too!

41:23.215 --> 41:26.182
- So...
- Roy?

41:26.184 --> 41:29.285
Right! It's my turn.

41:29.287 --> 41:30.986
Um...

41:30.988 --> 41:34.690
I'm thankful to both of you for
allowing me into your house

41:34.692 --> 41:35.860
this close to Christmas.

41:37.027 --> 41:39.131
I'm thankful for this food
you've put in front of me.

41:40.532 --> 41:43.233
I'm thankful to have met Emilia,

41:43.235 --> 41:44.567
who really is a sweetheart.

41:45.803 --> 41:49.539
And I'm thankful to know that
my family is alive and well,

41:49.541 --> 41:53.409
and I know they can't wait to see me when I
come home for Christmas in a couple days.

41:53.411 --> 41:56.479
You're supposed to see your
family in a couple days?

41:56.481 --> 41:58.448
I go home every year
for Christmas.

41:58.450 --> 42:00.018
I think
I told you that this morning.

42:00.919 --> 42:03.955
Have you ever
missed a Christmas?

42:05.190 --> 42:06.890
Not since my first year
out of college.

42:08.460 --> 42:10.393
My mother was furious.

42:10.395 --> 42:12.428
She took a picture
of my empty chair and wrote,

42:12.430 --> 42:14.998
"How about we just invite
the dog to come and eat?"

42:29.181 --> 42:30.614
I think everybody
else understood,

42:30.616 --> 42:32.315
but that didn't stop
the angry phone calls.

42:32.317 --> 42:33.783
Even if I didn't want to,

42:33.785 --> 42:36.620
I'd still go back just to prevent all
the bad blood for the next year.

42:36.622 --> 42:38.421
Oh.

42:38.423 --> 42:41.424
I wouldn't want your family
to be mad at you.

42:41.426 --> 42:42.692
They won't be.

42:42.694 --> 42:45.028
Because I'm going to go home
and spend Christmas with them.

42:45.030 --> 42:46.229
Roy?

42:46.231 --> 42:48.666
Anything else you're thankful for?
Or can we dig in?

42:48.668 --> 42:50.233
I'm done.

42:50.235 --> 42:52.971
Emilia, anything else
you wanted to do?

42:54.540 --> 42:56.839
Do you think Mom and Dad

42:56.841 --> 43:00.678
would have been sad if we
weren't at Christmas?

43:00.680 --> 43:02.078
What?

43:02.080 --> 43:04.615
I shouldn't have mentioned my parents.
I wasn't even thinking.

43:04.617 --> 43:06.617
How sad do you think
Mom and Dad would have been

43:06.619 --> 43:09.553
if they had Christmas
and we weren't there?

43:09.555 --> 43:11.422
Probably very sad.

43:11.424 --> 43:12.489
But it never happened.

43:12.491 --> 43:13.923
In fact,
the exact opposite happened.

43:13.925 --> 43:16.594
We've had lots and lots of
Christmases without Mom and Dad.

43:16.596 --> 43:18.195
I know!

43:18.197 --> 43:20.797
And it always makes me sad.

43:20.799 --> 43:22.799
I never thought about it
like that before.

43:22.801 --> 43:25.768
You shouldn't think about it!
You should be happy.

43:25.770 --> 43:26.670
We have a guest.

43:26.672 --> 43:27.971
Maybe we shouldn't.

43:27.973 --> 43:30.174
Maybe we shouldn't
have any more guests.

43:30.176 --> 43:31.342
Emilia, do you want me to leave?

43:31.344 --> 43:32.476
Shut up, Roy.

43:33.579 --> 43:34.580
Everything is okay.

43:36.148 --> 43:40.219
Mom and Dad are watching us, and they're
very happy that we're doing well.

43:43.956 --> 43:46.726
- You really think so?
- Yes!

43:50.963 --> 43:52.496
Okay.

43:56.102 --> 43:57.536
I didn't mean to offend anyone.

43:59.171 --> 44:01.505
Again, I can leave
if you want me to.

44:01.507 --> 44:03.476
- It seems like you two...
- I don't want you to leave!

44:10.549 --> 44:11.683
Then I'll stay.

44:28.401 --> 44:30.100
Mmh.

44:31.170 --> 44:32.436
Edward, you weren't lying.

44:32.438 --> 44:33.505
This soup is delicious.

44:33.507 --> 44:35.205
Thank you!

44:35.207 --> 44:36.541
You're welcome, Roy.

44:36.543 --> 44:38.510
Do you really like the soup,

44:38.512 --> 44:40.077
or are you just saying that?

44:40.079 --> 44:41.579
I like the soup.

44:41.581 --> 44:44.482
Because you don't have to eat
it if you don't like it.

44:44.484 --> 44:46.285
I really like it.

44:47.286 --> 44:51.358
Oh, okay. Good.

44:53.760 --> 44:54.858
Everything okay?

44:54.860 --> 44:58.465
Emilia, everything's okay,
correct?

45:04.771 --> 45:06.473
- Ooh!
- Oh.

45:07.774 --> 45:08.972
That scared me.

45:17.250 --> 45:18.819
Let's talk
about something happy.

45:19.786 --> 45:21.254
What's your happiest moment?

45:22.855 --> 45:25.557
There was one night,

45:25.559 --> 45:27.958
right after our uncle left,
and...

45:27.960 --> 45:30.028
...Edward took me outside and...

45:30.030 --> 45:32.097
...he put down a blanket and...

45:32.099 --> 45:34.432
...we laid down
and looked at the stars.

45:34.434 --> 45:37.602
And he told me that everything
was gonna be happy from now on.

45:37.604 --> 45:39.070
That no matter what happened,

45:39.072 --> 45:41.139
he would take care of me.

45:41.141 --> 45:44.709
And then we saw a shooting star,

45:44.711 --> 45:49.114
and he said that
that was probably our uncle,

45:49.116 --> 45:53.051
running away to be somewhere he
could finally be all alone, and...

45:53.053 --> 45:56.421
...not have to put up with
us stupid kids anymore.

45:56.423 --> 46:00.091
And Edward, he promised me that
there was a medicine I could take

46:00.093 --> 46:02.327
that could make me happy
all the time, so...

46:02.329 --> 46:05.597
...I wouldn't have to be sad
about anything ever again.

46:05.599 --> 46:08.133
And he promised he would
get it for me, and...

46:08.135 --> 46:12.270
...I knew that he really,
really meant it.

46:14.842 --> 46:16.274
That sounds really nice of him.

46:16.276 --> 46:17.442
It was.

46:17.444 --> 46:18.711
Here's the ham!

46:18.713 --> 46:20.713
Now, you both finish your soup

46:20.715 --> 46:21.714
and you can have some.

46:23.584 --> 46:25.350
Emilia was just telling me
about the promise

46:25.352 --> 46:27.820
you made her
after your uncle left.

46:27.822 --> 46:31.891
Which part? The medicine, or that
I would always be there for her?

46:31.893 --> 46:33.391
Both.

46:33.393 --> 46:34.729
Hmm.

46:36.029 --> 46:38.963
I've always been
interested in medicine.

46:38.965 --> 46:42.233
It fascinated me that we could
be sick, and then take a pill,

46:42.235 --> 46:43.602
and we would start
to get better.

46:43.604 --> 46:45.970
That there were things
outside of our bodies

46:45.972 --> 46:47.473
that we could put
into our bodies

46:47.475 --> 46:49.941
that would start to fix us.

46:49.943 --> 46:51.677
And I began to wonder

46:51.679 --> 46:54.946
what else I could fix
about myself.

46:54.948 --> 46:57.583
About Emilia. About everyone.

46:57.585 --> 46:59.017
So I began reading.

46:59.019 --> 47:03.689
I learned about a lot of different
medications for all sorts of things.

47:03.691 --> 47:06.592
Things you never thought
a drug could be used for.

47:06.594 --> 47:08.494
Like what?

47:08.496 --> 47:09.895
Well, the basics...

47:09.897 --> 47:13.265
...acetaminophen, diazepam,
haloperidol...

47:13.267 --> 47:15.367
...stopping a fever,

47:15.369 --> 47:18.372
pain relief, mental illness.

47:19.340 --> 47:22.074
There's erectile dysfunction,
obviously.

47:24.045 --> 47:26.512
Then there's
the really fascinating stuff.

47:26.514 --> 47:28.047
I never knew that you
could take a pill

47:28.049 --> 47:32.117
that would change
the way you see the world.

47:32.119 --> 47:34.720
Steroids, opiates,
hallucinogens.

47:34.722 --> 47:37.858
There are drugs that makes it
so you can't feel pain.

47:37.860 --> 47:39.758
Drugs that make you forget.

47:39.760 --> 47:41.393
Drugs that make you tired.

47:43.531 --> 47:47.366
So now Edward
works with medicine.

47:47.368 --> 47:48.802
You started taking medicine
after that?

47:48.804 --> 47:50.236
Every day.

47:50.238 --> 47:51.403
How old were you
when this happened?

47:51.405 --> 47:53.005
She was 12.
I was 17.

47:53.007 --> 47:54.875
That's awfully young
to be taking medication.

47:54.877 --> 47:57.142
Well, we both turned out okay.

47:57.144 --> 47:59.946
Yeah, you two
seem really normal.

47:59.948 --> 48:02.581
Roy! What do you want to do
after dinner?

48:02.583 --> 48:04.618
Oh, Emilia.
Give the guy a break.

48:04.620 --> 48:06.285
I figure I'd head home.

48:06.287 --> 48:07.854
Start packing.

48:07.856 --> 48:09.388
Do you have to?

48:09.390 --> 48:12.959
Let's just wait and see
how he feels after dinner.

48:12.961 --> 48:14.628
Okay.

48:14.630 --> 48:20.634
I just thought he might want to
play with my Christmas present.

48:20.636 --> 48:23.436
That's right.
The one you opened early.

48:23.438 --> 48:24.203
What is it?

48:24.205 --> 48:27.007
Don't spoil the surprise.

48:27.009 --> 48:28.842
I won't.

48:28.844 --> 48:30.644
I think you're really
going to like it.

48:30.646 --> 48:32.111
Yeah?

48:32.113 --> 48:34.648
Yeah! I think you might even
want to stay

48:34.650 --> 48:38.150
and play with
it for a really long time.

48:40.422 --> 48:41.523
Sounds fun.

48:48.162 --> 48:50.095
Looks like I'm
ready for a piece of that ham.

48:50.097 --> 48:51.833
So you are.

48:54.101 --> 48:55.535
Mmh.

49:10.852 --> 49:12.454
Roy?

49:15.557 --> 49:18.061
Sorry. I don't know
what just happened.

49:19.996 --> 49:22.997
- - Emilia? Some ham?
- Yes, please.

49:24.499 --> 49:27.235
- - Emilia? Some ham?
- Yes, please.

49:31.007 --> 49:32.372
Thank you very much.

49:32.374 --> 49:34.407
I'm glad your mood has improved.

49:34.409 --> 49:36.978
Well, I just remembered
how much fun

49:36.980 --> 49:39.312
Roy is
going to have with my toy.

49:39.314 --> 49:40.982
Hmm.

49:40.984 --> 49:42.215
Where is this toy?

49:42.217 --> 49:43.720
In the garage.

49:45.287 --> 49:47.354
So it's a big toy.

49:47.356 --> 49:50.091
It's really big.

49:55.064 --> 49:56.664
I love your giggle.

49:56.666 --> 49:58.065
You do?

49:58.067 --> 49:59.667
It's adorable.

49:59.669 --> 50:01.501
Now you sound like Jason.

50:11.748 --> 50:14.649
Is that what Jason said to you
in the parking lot

50:14.651 --> 50:17.418
when you met him
at the pharmacy?

50:17.420 --> 50:19.354
Yeah, yes.

50:20.322 --> 50:24.592
I laughed.
When he was asking me out I...

50:24.594 --> 50:27.463
I laughed, or giggled.

50:28.564 --> 50:30.400
He said he loved it.

50:31.100 --> 50:33.434
Sounds just like Jason.

50:33.436 --> 50:35.203
Always the smooth talker.

50:36.406 --> 50:38.773
I never did meet this Jason guy.

50:38.775 --> 50:41.711
No, you wouldn't have.

50:43.279 --> 50:45.079
He's something else.

50:45.081 --> 50:47.214
I just feel bad
for his girlfriend.

50:49.318 --> 50:51.654
It's probably for the best
you never met.

50:59.063 --> 51:01.762
This ham is really delicious.

51:01.764 --> 51:03.999
Thank you, Roy.

51:04.001 --> 51:06.103
I spent a lot of time on it.

51:09.006 --> 51:11.106
I almost forgot, Emilia,

51:11.108 --> 51:13.374
I got you a Christmas present,
but I...

51:13.376 --> 51:15.209
...left it in the car.

51:15.211 --> 51:18.713
Oh, you didn't
have to get me anything.

51:18.715 --> 51:21.315
I know, but I wanted
to get you something as a...

51:21.317 --> 51:24.285
...as a thank you for inviting
me over for dinner tonight.

51:24.287 --> 51:26.387
I can go grab it...

51:26.389 --> 51:28.456
...and then you can show me
your Christmas present!

51:28.458 --> 51:30.624
What a fantastic idea.

51:57.988 --> 51:58.987
I'm sorry.

51:58.989 --> 52:00.354
I had to.

52:07.396 --> 52:09.865
You killed him!
You killed him!

52:09.867 --> 52:10.866
I had to.

52:10.868 --> 52:12.134
I had to.

52:12.136 --> 52:13.537
Why!?

52:14.471 --> 52:17.572
He was going to stay here
and be my toy!

52:17.574 --> 52:18.874
It was the only way.

52:22.813 --> 52:25.647
I don't understand
why you had to kill him!

52:25.649 --> 52:27.349
Put him up on the table.

52:29.720 --> 52:32.053
Pull him.

52:36.426 --> 52:39.162
What are we going
to do with him?

52:39.164 --> 52:42.165
He isn't going to make it
home for Christmas.

52:42.167 --> 52:44.666
His family is
gonna be so mad at him.

52:44.668 --> 52:46.802
Don't worry about his family
right now, Emilia.

52:46.804 --> 52:48.906
We need to deal with this.

52:49.773 --> 52:52.277
Don't let him
fall off the table.

52:54.378 --> 52:55.944
What are you going to do
with that?!

52:55.946 --> 52:57.579
He'll be easier to bury.
And harder to find.

52:59.449 --> 53:01.184
You're going to bury him?!

53:01.186 --> 53:03.485
I really wish you didn't
have to see this right now.

53:03.487 --> 53:05.087
But this is what happens

53:05.089 --> 53:06.655
when you do things
without telling me first.

53:06.657 --> 53:07.892
Do you understand?

53:09.526 --> 53:11.395
This is my fault.

53:12.429 --> 53:13.996
Don't think about it that way.

53:13.998 --> 53:18.567
This is what happens when toys stop
working the way they're supposed to.

53:18.569 --> 53:20.870
Is this what happened
to all my other toys?

53:20.872 --> 53:23.538
You have to understand,
when somebody becomes a toy,

53:23.540 --> 53:25.174
the rules change.

53:25.176 --> 53:26.374
You can't murder a toy.

53:26.376 --> 53:27.509
I didn't kill Roy.

53:29.613 --> 53:31.613
Is this going
to happen to Jason?

53:31.615 --> 53:33.249
When he stops working
the way he's supposed to,

53:33.251 --> 53:34.650
but as long
as I give him medicine,

53:34.652 --> 53:37.053
you'll be able to play with him
a while longer.

53:55.473 --> 53:58.441
- Is it another girl?
- I thought you didn't want to know any details.

53:58.443 --> 54:00.843
You're right, I don't. But if
you're fucking around on Kate...

54:00.845 --> 54:02.478
What does it matter to you?

54:02.480 --> 54:04.146
It really feels like you're not
on my side here.

54:04.148 --> 54:05.548
Why does there have to be sides?

54:05.550 --> 54:06.616
I don't know!

54:06.618 --> 54:08.751
Why are you taking one?
And why isn't it mine?

54:08.753 --> 54:10.820
I'm not saying
that's what's happening.

54:10.822 --> 54:13.656
I'm just saying,
if you are cheating...

54:13.658 --> 54:16.726
It's like you're in love with my
girlfriend, or something.

54:16.728 --> 54:18.696
You in love with my girlfriend,
Roy?

54:24.802 --> 54:28.504
Oh, my...
This explains so much.

54:28.506 --> 54:29.507
Drop it.

54:30.808 --> 54:32.975
You don't have to worry about it
'cause it's not another girl.

54:32.977 --> 54:34.677
I wish I could believe that.

54:34.679 --> 54:36.746
Fucking hell, Roy.

54:36.748 --> 54:40.950
I came here to give you a heads up.
I'm not even sure if I'm going.

54:40.952 --> 54:42.019
You know, you don't deserve her.

54:42.021 --> 54:43.287
I know.

54:43.289 --> 54:45.355
And if this "going off the grid"
thing doesn't work out...

54:45.357 --> 54:47.157
What?

54:47.159 --> 54:48.858
You'll what?

54:48.860 --> 54:50.027
Huh?

54:50.029 --> 54:52.996
You think if Kate weren't
with me, she'd be with you?

54:52.998 --> 54:54.497
- She'd never be with you.
- Fuck you!

54:54.499 --> 54:56.001
You know I'm right.

54:57.568 --> 55:00.137
- I'm not lying for you anymore.
- Then don't!

55:00.139 --> 55:02.041
She'll hate you, too.

55:02.908 --> 55:05.474
Fuck, Roy.

55:05.476 --> 55:07.413
I'm not going to fight with you
like this.

55:08.546 --> 55:11.348
I came over here to give you
coffee and doughnuts,

55:11.350 --> 55:13.951
and you're dropping bombs
on me, man.

55:13.953 --> 55:16.654
You're supposed to be
my best friend.

55:20.658 --> 55:23.162
Enjoy the fucking doughnuts.

55:40.045 --> 55:44.216
So...
what was wrong with this toy?

55:45.617 --> 55:47.150
The medicine wasn't working.

55:47.152 --> 55:48.919
It was making him
into something else.

55:48.921 --> 55:50.921
Something scary.

55:50.923 --> 55:52.189
Really?

55:52.191 --> 55:53.557
Yes.

55:53.559 --> 55:55.726
I couldn't even tell.

55:55.728 --> 55:57.327
That's why you need me.

55:57.329 --> 55:59.932
To keep you safe from the
ones that don't work.

56:01.233 --> 56:02.833
It's okay.

56:02.835 --> 56:03.700
Hey.

56:03.702 --> 56:06.136
Why don't you go
and tidy up the house,

56:06.138 --> 56:08.239
and bring the knife up there,

56:08.241 --> 56:10.807
then you can come back in
and play with your toy.

56:10.809 --> 56:12.745
Might make you feel better.

56:14.880 --> 56:17.714
Here. Take the knife
back to the house.

56:17.716 --> 56:19.384
Okay.

56:19.386 --> 56:21.051
I will.

56:21.053 --> 56:22.919
Thanks.

57:45.372 --> 57:47.140
Do you know
what I learned tonight?

57:49.909 --> 57:54.178
I learned that one day...

57:54.180 --> 57:55.982
...you're going to break.

57:57.217 --> 58:00.452
And then you'll have to die...

58:00.454 --> 58:02.722
...like the rest of my toys.

58:04.325 --> 58:06.090
But that's okay.

58:06.092 --> 58:08.693
Because I'm gonna love you

58:08.695 --> 58:12.098
and play with you all the way
until that happens.

58:14.535 --> 58:16.803
<i>I didn't understand before...</i>

58:17.770 --> 58:20.074
<i>...why my toys would disappear.</i>

58:21.442 --> 58:24.911
<i>Christmas would come and go...</i>

58:26.113 --> 58:28.746
...and I'd have my toy and...

58:28.748 --> 58:32.586
...then one morning,
it would be gone.

58:34.522 --> 58:37.124
Edward always said they broke.

58:38.092 --> 58:40.758
<i>I thought that was weird,</i>

58:40.760 --> 58:44.532
<i>because I've played
with broken toys before.</i>

58:47.034 --> 58:50.471
<i>But... I get it now.</i>

58:53.007 --> 58:56.544
<i>Broken... means dead.</i>

58:58.112 --> 59:00.247
<i>Like my parents.</i>

59:03.918 --> 59:05.886
I'm going to miss you
when you break.

59:10.391 --> 59:11.992
You're fun.

59:19.833 --> 59:21.969
You want to know a secret?

59:25.540 --> 59:27.908
You're my favorite.

59:32.746 --> 59:35.914
I think I want to have some fun
right now.

59:55.069 --> 59:56.802
That feels so good.

01:00:07.115 --> 01:00:08.483
Why do you like me?

01:00:10.452 --> 01:00:11.850
Don't even ask that question.

01:00:11.852 --> 01:00:13.553
I already asked it.

01:00:13.555 --> 01:00:15.022
Well, it's a stupid question.

01:00:17.225 --> 01:00:19.125
I need an answer.

01:00:22.731 --> 01:00:24.364
I just do.

01:00:31.306 --> 01:00:33.506
Come on.
Check it later.

01:00:33.508 --> 01:00:34.374
Could be important.

01:00:42.384 --> 01:00:43.683
Is it important?

01:00:43.685 --> 01:00:45.587
Not in the slightest.

01:00:47.422 --> 01:00:49.088
You were right.

01:00:49.090 --> 01:00:50.556
I always am.

01:01:02.638 --> 01:01:04.270
Tell me you like it.

01:01:04.272 --> 01:01:06.174
I like it a lot.

01:01:11.614 --> 01:01:14.215
Do you like when I do this?

01:01:15.417 --> 01:01:17.417
You know I do.

01:01:29.030 --> 01:01:31.632
- Oh, God.
- You have to wait.

01:01:31.634 --> 01:01:32.932
Oh, yeah.

01:01:38.273 --> 01:01:40.141
What did you say?

01:01:45.348 --> 01:01:47.115
I can make it feel better.

01:01:48.284 --> 01:01:53.422
I can make the game more fun
if you help me.

01:01:58.893 --> 01:02:00.463
That feels good.

01:02:02.465 --> 01:02:04.100
Will you help me?

01:02:05.401 --> 01:02:06.767
Help you what?

01:02:06.769 --> 01:02:08.502
Get out of here.

01:02:08.504 --> 01:02:10.473
I don't want you to leave.

01:02:11.540 --> 01:02:12.907
I do.

01:02:15.244 --> 01:02:16.744
What are you...

01:02:16.746 --> 01:02:18.779
I don't like that.

01:02:18.781 --> 01:02:21.348
It'll feel good.
It'll feel good, I promise.

01:02:35.631 --> 01:02:37.464
Let me try something else.

01:02:37.466 --> 01:02:39.268
- Okay?
- What?

01:02:40.269 --> 01:02:42.069
I have to get on top.

01:02:43.973 --> 01:02:46.275
I'm sorry! I didn't mean...

01:02:47.543 --> 01:02:50.012
I don't think I like
this game anymore.

01:04:12.662 --> 01:04:16.064
Fuck, yes!
Fuck, yes!

01:04:26.676 --> 01:04:28.243
Emilia...

01:04:28.245 --> 01:04:29.945
Emilia.

01:04:29.947 --> 01:04:31.181
Emilia!

01:04:32.082 --> 01:04:34.249
Why aren't you playing
with your toy?

01:04:34.251 --> 01:04:36.351
I don't want to anymore.

01:04:36.353 --> 01:04:38.721
Because now you know
what's going to happen to him?

01:04:38.723 --> 01:04:40.789
He's already broken.

01:04:40.791 --> 01:04:43.024
What do you mean, he's broken?

01:04:43.026 --> 01:04:45.126
He did what he
wasn't supposed to do.

01:04:45.128 --> 01:04:48.631
Come on. Come on, pick
up the fucking phone.

01:04:50.801 --> 01:04:52.200
Come on!

01:04:54.972 --> 01:04:57.940
Jason? Where are you!?

01:04:57.942 --> 01:05:00.910
I'm so fucking mad at you right now.
You have no idea...

01:05:00.912 --> 01:05:02.613
Help me!

01:05:03.447 --> 01:05:05.948
Oh, my God, Jason?
Are you okay?

01:05:05.950 --> 01:05:08.118
I'm kidnapped.

01:05:08.886 --> 01:05:10.419
Need rescue.

01:05:10.421 --> 01:05:11.754
Oh, my God! Jason!

01:05:11.756 --> 01:05:12.788
Where are you?!

01:05:12.790 --> 01:05:14.255
Hurry!

01:05:14.257 --> 01:05:17.560
I need you to tell me
exactly what you mean.

01:05:17.562 --> 01:05:18.827
Is Jason alive?

01:05:18.829 --> 01:05:21.764
No, he's a toy,

01:05:21.766 --> 01:05:24.065
and he doesn't work anymore.

01:05:24.067 --> 01:05:25.469
What part doesn't work?

01:05:27.137 --> 01:05:28.906
It wasn't right!

01:05:29.774 --> 01:05:32.043
I wasn't playing with him,
he was...

01:05:34.011 --> 01:05:35.811
...playing with me!

01:05:43.654 --> 01:05:45.287
Okay, Jason,
I need you to call...

01:05:45.289 --> 01:05:46.522
I need you to tell me
where you are,

01:05:46.524 --> 01:05:48.123
because I need to know
where you are

01:05:48.125 --> 01:05:49.124
so I can come
and get you!

01:05:49.126 --> 01:05:50.626
As fast as you can.

01:05:50.628 --> 01:05:52.030
<i>I'm gonna call the police!</i>

01:05:53.364 --> 01:05:55.598
<i>Wait, wait, Jason! You have
to tell me where you are.</i>

01:05:55.600 --> 01:05:57.968
Don't call back.

01:05:57.970 --> 01:05:59.201
Find my phone.

01:06:02.306 --> 01:06:05.441
Wait, wait.
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

01:06:05.443 --> 01:06:08.377
- What the fuck did you do?
- Wait, wait.

01:06:08.379 --> 01:06:10.312
Yes,
I'd like to report a kidnapping.

01:06:10.314 --> 01:06:12.314
Uh, it's my boyfriend,
Jason Lowe...

01:06:12.316 --> 01:06:13.649
He's been missing
for three days,

01:06:13.651 --> 01:06:16.218
and he just called and told me
that he'd been kidnapped!

01:06:16.220 --> 01:06:19.455
Yes, I understand
how that sounds.

01:06:19.457 --> 01:06:23.059
Look, I would appreciate you
taking this fucking seriously!

01:06:23.061 --> 01:06:24.894
Look, okay, I have the address
where he's being held

01:06:24.896 --> 01:06:26.228
and I'm gonna there now.

01:06:26.230 --> 01:06:27.864
Fuck no,
I won't stay here!

01:06:27.866 --> 01:06:30.366
- What the fuck did you do?!
- It was an accident!

01:06:30.368 --> 01:06:32.836
- How did you get untied?
- Emilia.

01:06:32.838 --> 01:06:34.873
- Why?
- She wanted to cuddle.

01:06:35.841 --> 01:06:37.573
What are you doing
all the way over here?

01:06:37.575 --> 01:06:39.876
I didn't do anything, I swear. I
was just trying to make her happy

01:06:39.878 --> 01:06:40.910
so I didn't end up like Roy.

01:06:40.912 --> 01:06:42.177
She said you were broken.

01:06:42.179 --> 01:06:43.613
I don't know what that means.

01:06:43.615 --> 01:06:46.215
- I just tried to make her happy, I swear.
- How? How?!

01:06:46.217 --> 01:06:48.384
By giving her more pleasure.

01:06:48.386 --> 01:06:50.820
She doesn't like when things
don't play by her rules.

01:06:50.822 --> 01:06:52.555
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to scare her.

01:06:52.557 --> 01:06:55.525
I just wanted to make her happy!

01:06:55.527 --> 01:06:57.494
I have to tie you back up.

01:06:57.496 --> 01:07:00.397
No, please, please, please!

01:07:00.399 --> 01:07:02.732
I'm not going to do anything.
I can't do anything.

01:07:02.734 --> 01:07:05.101
It's one thing!
Just give me this one thing.

01:07:05.103 --> 01:07:06.469
- Please.
- I can't do that.

01:07:06.471 --> 01:07:08.805
